The recent arXiv paper "Value Bonuses using Ensemble Errors for Exploration in Reinforcement Learning" by Abdul Wahab, Raksha Kumaraswamy, and Martha White proposes a new approach to directed exploration in reinforcement learning. The authors introduce an algorithm called Value Bonuses with Ensemble errors (VBE) that maintains a value bonus for each state-action pair, which is updated based on the ensemble errors of the value function estimates.

The VBE algorithm encourages the agent to visit new states and actions by increasing the value bonus for unvisited state-action pairs. This approach is more efficient than traditional methods, such as optimistic value estimates, which only increase the value bonus retroactively after seeing a higher reward bonus.

The authors demonstrate the effectiveness of VBE in several benchmark environments, showing that it outperforms other exploration strategies in terms of cumulative rewards and visitation counts.

Overall, this paper provides a new perspective on directed exploration in reinforcement learning and offers a promising approach for improving the efficiency of RL algorithms.